{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/172/comments/3600786.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/172#comment-3600786"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim/issues/172.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 172, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/drcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/drcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "drcsim", "full_name": "osrf/drcsim", "uuid": "{247b5408-ae91-4e3c-b2f9-a21994658d11}"}, "title": "Safety limits out of range"}, "content": {"raw": "Back in December (part of #55) the reason for not changing this to within hard limits was that the safety controller would kick in, complicating the dynamics system. Given that the system isn't using the PR2 controllers any longer I suppose this can be changed now?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Back in December (part of <a href=\"#!/osrf/drcsim/issues/55/bdi-cfg-parser-precision\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"BDI cfg parser precision\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#55</s></a>) the reason for not changing this to within hard limits was that the safety controller would kick in, complicating the dynamics system. Given that the system isn't using the PR2 controllers any longer I suppose this can be changed now?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-04-03T03:51:46.596434+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Thomas Koletschka", "uuid": "{b33092ac-6376-48d1-9803-d9e6de445d1a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bb33092ac-6376-48d1-9803-d9e6de445d1a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bb33092ac-6376-48d1-9803-d9e6de445d1a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/account/thomasko/avatar/"}}, "nickname": "thomasko", "type": "user", "account_id": null}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 3600786}